{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":600,"text":"Imagine that when you walked\nin here this evening,"},{"time":3440,"text":"you discovered that everybody in the room\nlooked almost exactly the same:"},{"time":8280,"text":"ageless, raceless,"},{"time":10240,"text":"generically good-looking."},{"time":12280,"text":"That person sitting right next to you"},{"time":14280,"text":"might have the most\nidiosyncratic inner life,"},{"time":16440,"text":"but you don't have a clue"},{"time":17720,"text":"because we're all wearing\nthe same blank expression all the time."},{"time":22960,"text":"That is the kind of creepy transformation\nthat is taking over cities,"},{"time":27920,"text":"only it applies to buildings, not people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31480,"text":"Cities are full of roughness and shadow,"},{"time":37480,"text":"texture and color."},{"time":38720,"text":"You can still find architectural surfaces\nof great individuality and character"},{"time":45360,"text":"in apartment buildings in Riga"},{"time":48080,"text":"and Yemen,"},{"time":50520,"text":"social housing in Vienna,"},{"time":53000,"text":"Hopi villages in Arizona,"},{"time":55400,"text":"brownstones in New York,"},{"time":57520,"text":"wooden houses in San Francisco."},{"time":59800,"text":"These aren't palaces or cathedrals."},{"time":62080,"text":"These are just ordinary residences"},{"time":63880,"text":"expressing the ordinary\nsplendor of cities."},{"time":67480,"text":"And the reason they're like that\nis that the need for shelter"},{"time":70800,"text":"is so bound up with\nthe human desire for beauty."},{"time":76600,"text":"Their rough surfaces\ngive us a touchable city."},{"time":80840,"text":"Right? Streets that you can read"},{"time":82440,"text":"by running your fingers\nover brick and stone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85600,"text":"But that's getting harder to do,"},{"time":88200,"text":"because cities are becoming smooth."},{"time":91680,"text":"New downtowns sprout towers"},{"time":93760,"text":"that are almost always\nmade of concrete and steel"},{"time":96120,"text":"and covered in glass."},{"time":98920,"text":"You can look at skylines\nall over the world --"},{"time":101800,"text":"Houston,"},{"time":103640,"text":"Guangzhou,"},{"time":105440,"text":"Frankfurt --"},{"time":107440,"text":"and you see the same army\nof high-gloss robots"},{"time":110880,"text":"marching over the horizon."},{"time":113560,"text":"Now, just think of everything we lose"},{"time":115720,"text":"when architects stop using\nthe full range of available materials."},{"time":120800,"text":"When we reject granite\nand limestone and sandstone"},{"time":124560,"text":"and wood and copper\nand terra-cotta and brick"},{"time":126760,"text":"and wattle and plaster,"},{"time":129120,"text":"we simplify architecture"},{"time":131280,"text":"and we impoverish cities."},{"time":133880,"text":"It's as if you reduced\nall of the world's cuisines"},{"time":137600,"text":"down to airline food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":140640,"text":"Chicken or pasta?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":143440,"text":"But worse still,"},{"time":145760,"text":"assemblies of glass towers\nlike this one in Moscow"},{"time":149360,"text":"suggest a disdain for the civic\nand communal aspects of urban living."},{"time":154280,"text":"Right? Buildings like these are intended\nto enrich their owners and tenants,"},{"time":159360,"text":"but not necessarily\nthe lives of the rest of us,"},{"time":161960,"text":"those of us who navigate\nthe spaces between the buildings."},{"time":166440,"text":"And we expect to do so for free."},{"time":169800,"text":"Shiny towers are an invasive species"},{"time":173080,"text":"and they are choking our cities\nand killing off public space."},{"time":177320,"text":"We tend to think of a facade\nas being like makeup,"},{"time":180800,"text":"a decorative layer applied at the end\nto a building that's effectively complete."},{"time":185160,"text":"But just because a facade is superficial"},{"time":187720,"text":"doesn't mean it's not also deep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"Let me give you an example"},{"time":192200,"text":"of how a city's surfaces\naffect the way we live in it."},{"time":195240,"text":"When I visited Salamanca in Spain,"},{"time":198160,"text":"I gravitated to the Plaza Mayor"},{"time":200440,"text":"at all hours of the day."},{"time":201880,"text":"Early in the morning,\nsunlight rakes the facades,"},{"time":204880,"text":"sharpening shadows,"},{"time":206600,"text":"and at night, lamplight\nsegments the buildings"},{"time":209920,"text":"into hundreds of distinct areas,"},{"time":212520,"text":"balconies and windows and arcades,"},{"time":214920,"text":"each one a separate pocket\nof visual activity."},{"time":218680,"text":"That detail and depth, that glamour"},{"time":222640,"text":"gives the plaza a theatrical quality."},{"time":227000,"text":"It becomes a stage\nwhere the generations can meet."},{"time":230160,"text":"You have teenagers\nsprawling on the pavers,"},{"time":233560,"text":"seniors monopolizing the benches,"},{"time":236400,"text":"and real life starts to look\nlike an opera set."},{"time":240320,"text":"The curtain goes up on Salamanca."},{"time":243520,"text":"So just because I'm talking\nabout the exteriors of buildings,"},{"time":248520,"text":"not form, not function, not structure,"},{"time":252760,"text":"even so those surfaces\ngive texture to our lives,"},{"time":257399,"text":"because buildings\ncreate the spaces around them,"},{"time":260320,"text":"and those spaces can draw people in"},{"time":263360,"text":"or push them away."},{"time":265280,"text":"And the difference often has to do\nwith the quality of those exteriors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269000,"text":"So one contemporary equivalent\nof the Plaza Mayor in Salamanca"},{"time":272760,"text":"is the Place de la DÃ©fense in Paris,"},{"time":275880,"text":"a windswept, glass-walled open space"},{"time":279520,"text":"that office workers hurry through"},{"time":281320,"text":"on the way from the metro\nto their cubicles"},{"time":283840,"text":"but otherwise spend\nas little time in as possible."},{"time":288120,"text":"In the early 1980s,\nthe architect Philip Johnson"},{"time":291440,"text":"tried to recreate a gracious\nEuropean plaza in Pittsburgh."},{"time":295680,"text":"This is PPG Place,"},{"time":297200,"text":"a half acre of open space\nencircled by commercial buildings"},{"time":302440,"text":"made of mirrored glass."},{"time":303920,"text":"And he ornamented those buildings\nwith metal trim and bays"},{"time":307360,"text":"and Gothic turrets"},{"time":309320,"text":"which really pop on the skyline."},{"time":311880,"text":"But at ground level,"},{"time":314520,"text":"the plaza feels like a black glass cage."},{"time":318080,"text":"I mean, sure, in summertime"},{"time":319960,"text":"kids are running back and forth\nthrough the fountain"},{"time":322440,"text":"and there's ice-skating in the winter,"},{"time":324440,"text":"but it lacks the informality\nof a leisurely hangout."},{"time":327680,"text":"It's just not the sort of place\nyou really want to just hang out and chat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335480,"text":"Public spaces thrive or fail\nfor many different reasons."},{"time":339240,"text":"Architecture is only one,"},{"time":341480,"text":"but it's an important one."},{"time":343840,"text":"Some recent plazas"},{"time":345200,"text":"like Federation Square in Melbourne"},{"time":348640,"text":"or Superkilen in Copenhagen"},{"time":351960,"text":"succeed because they combine old and new,"},{"time":355360,"text":"rough and smooth,"},{"time":357400,"text":"neutral and bright colors,"},{"time":359280,"text":"and because they don't rely\nexcessively on glass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364000,"text":"Now, I'm not against glass."},{"time":367800,"text":"It's an ancient and versatile material."},{"time":371640,"text":"It's easy to manufacture and transport"},{"time":375880,"text":"and install and replace"},{"time":377960,"text":"and clean."},{"time":379520,"text":"It comes in everything\nfrom enormous, ultraclear sheets"},{"time":382440,"text":"to translucent bricks."},{"time":385200,"text":"New coatings make it change mood"},{"time":387520,"text":"in the shifting light."},{"time":389880,"text":"In expensive cities like New York,\nit has the magical power"},{"time":393160,"text":"of being able to multiply\nreal estate values by allowing views,"},{"time":396800,"text":"which is really the only commodity\nthat developers have to offer"},{"time":399920,"text":"to justify those surreal prices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404400,"text":"In the middle of the 19th century,"},{"time":406360,"text":"with the construction\nof the Crystal Palace in London,"},{"time":409160,"text":"glass leapt to the top of the list\nof quintessentially modern substances."},{"time":414280,"text":"By the mid-20th century,"},{"time":415800,"text":"it had come to dominate\nthe downtowns of some American cities,"},{"time":419680,"text":"largely through some\nreally spectacular office buildings"},{"time":422720,"text":"like Lever House in midtown Manhattan,\ndesigned by Skidmore, Owings and Merrill."},{"time":427560,"text":"Eventually, the technology\nadvanced to the point"},{"time":430280,"text":"where architects could design\nstructures so transparent"},{"time":433400,"text":"they practically disappear."},{"time":436360,"text":"And along the way,"},{"time":437800,"text":"glass became the default material\nof the high-rise city,"},{"time":442680,"text":"and there's a very\npowerful reason for that."},{"time":445200,"text":"Because as the world's populations\nconverge on cities,"},{"time":450000,"text":"the least fortunate pack\ninto jerry-built shantytowns."},{"time":453680,"text":"But hundreds of millions of people\nneed apartments and places to work"},{"time":457520,"text":"in ever-larger buildings,"},{"time":458760,"text":"so it makes economic sense\nto put up towers"},{"time":461400,"text":"and wrap them in cheap\nand practical curtain walls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465600,"text":"But glass has a limited ability"},{"time":469080,"text":"to be expressive."},{"time":471240,"text":"This is a section of wall framing a plaza"},{"time":473440,"text":"in the pre-Hispanic city of Mitla,\nin southern Mexico."},{"time":478640,"text":"Those 2,000-year-old carvings"},{"time":480160,"text":"make it clear that this was a place\nof high ritual significance."},{"time":485240,"text":"Today we look at those and we can see\na historical and textural continuity"},{"time":491040,"text":"between those carvings,\nthe mountains all around"},{"time":493920,"text":"and that church which is built\non top of the ruins"},{"time":497800,"text":"using stone plundered from the site."},{"time":500880,"text":"In nearby Oaxaca,\neven ordinary plaster buildings"},{"time":503800,"text":"become canvasses for\nbright colors, political murals"},{"time":508160,"text":"and sophisticated graphic arts."},{"time":511000,"text":"It's an intricate, communicative language"},{"time":514400,"text":"that an epidemic of glass\nwould simply wipe out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517960,"text":"The good news is\nthat architects and developers"},{"time":520760,"text":"have begun to rediscover\nthe joys of texture"},{"time":523760,"text":"without backing away from modernity."},{"time":526240,"text":"Some find innovative uses\nfor old materials like brick"},{"time":531320,"text":"and terra-cotta."},{"time":533760,"text":"Others invent new products\nlike the molded panels that SnÃ¸hetta used"},{"time":539080,"text":"to give the San Francisco\nMuseum of Modern Art"},{"time":541520,"text":"that crinkly, sculptural quality."},{"time":544520,"text":"The architect Stefano Boeri\neven created living facades."},{"time":548440,"text":"This is his Vertical Forest,\na pair of apartment towers in Milan,"},{"time":552480,"text":"whose most visible feature is greenery."},{"time":555240,"text":"And Boeri is designing a version of this\nfor Nanjing in China."},{"time":561080,"text":"And imagine if green facades\nwere as ubiquitous as glass ones"},{"time":565240,"text":"how much cleaner the air\nin Chinese cities would become."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569280,"text":"But the truth is\nthat these are mostly one-offs,"},{"time":572320,"text":"boutique projects,"},{"time":573840,"text":"not easily reproduced at a global scale."},{"time":577720,"text":"And that is the point."},{"time":580360,"text":"When you use materials\nthat have a local significance,"},{"time":583480,"text":"you prevent cities\nfrom all looking the same."},{"time":586760,"text":"Copper has a long history in New York --"},{"time":589640,"text":"the Statue of Liberty,"},{"time":591720,"text":"the crown of the Woolworth Building --"},{"time":594200,"text":"but it fell out of fashion for a long time"},{"time":597400,"text":"until SHoP Architects used it\nto cover the American Copper Building,"},{"time":601800,"text":"a pair of twisting towers\non the East River."},{"time":605160,"text":"It's not even finished"},{"time":606440,"text":"and you can see the way\nsunset lights up that metallic facade,"},{"time":610560,"text":"which will weather to green as it ages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613720,"text":"Buildings can be like people."},{"time":616040,"text":"Their faces broadcast their experience."},{"time":619400,"text":"And that's an important point,"},{"time":620880,"text":"because when glass ages,"},{"time":623800,"text":"you just replace it,"},{"time":625320,"text":"and the building looks\npretty much the same way it did before"},{"time":628240,"text":"until eventually it's demolished."},{"time":629960,"text":"Almost all other materials\nhave the ability"},{"time":632760,"text":"to absorb infusions of history and memory,"},{"time":636360,"text":"and project it into the present."},{"time":640840,"text":"The firm Ennead"},{"time":642720,"text":"clad the Utah Natural History Museum\nin Salt Lake City in copper and zinc,"},{"time":647640,"text":"ores that have been mined\nin the area for 150 years"},{"time":653280,"text":"and that also camouflage the building\nagainst the ochre hills"},{"time":657360,"text":"so that you have a natural history museum"},{"time":659680,"text":"that reflects the region's\nnatural history."},{"time":663680,"text":"And when the Chinese\nPritzker Prize winner Wang Shu"},{"time":666480,"text":"was building a history museum in Ningbo,"},{"time":669840,"text":"he didn't just create\na wrapper for the past,"},{"time":673080,"text":"he built memory right into the walls"},{"time":676160,"text":"by using brick and stones and shingles"},{"time":679880,"text":"salvaged from villages\nthat had been demolished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684440,"text":"Now, architects can use glass"},{"time":687320,"text":"in equally lyrical and inventive ways."},{"time":690120,"text":"Here in New York, two buildings,"},{"time":691840,"text":"one by Jean Nouvel\nand this one by Frank Gehry"},{"time":695160,"text":"face off across West 19th Street,"},{"time":697800,"text":"and the play of reflections\nthat they toss back and forth"},{"time":700760,"text":"is like a symphony in light."},{"time":704280,"text":"But when a city defaults to glass"},{"time":707320,"text":"as it grows,"},{"time":708840,"text":"it becomes a hall of mirrors,"},{"time":711080,"text":"disquieting and cold."},{"time":714000,"text":"After all, cities are places\nof concentrated variety"},{"time":719680,"text":"where the world's cultures\nand languages and lifestyles"},{"time":724720,"text":"come together and mingle."},{"time":727000,"text":"So rather than encase all that variety"},{"time":730800,"text":"and diversity in buildings\nof crushing sameness,"},{"time":734800,"text":"we should have an architecture that honors\nthe full range of the urban experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741240,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}